  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Strategy :<br>
The goal of this deck is to significantly slow your opponent while you travel the lands with your hobbits and rangers.<br>
<br>
Bid 4, as you can remove the four tokens before the end of the first turn. Choose to go first to put East Road into play. You may screw your opponent if he had planned to play Prancing Pony, and even if he has a companion in hand, he&#8217;ll think twice before playing it (+2 to twilight cost may pay a minion&#8217;s roaming cost). If opponent bids higher that 4, it&#8217;ll nasty for him regarding the three Enduring Evil you&#8217;ll play. :-)<br>
<br>
Start with the hobbits. Hopefully you&#8217;ll draw Thror&#8217;s Map first hand to play your site 2 where no skirmish may take place. However, if you haven&#8217;t got Thror&#8217;s Map, you won&#8217;t be crushed : Sam and Pippin are ideal cannon fodder once they&#8217;ve done their jobs. Don&#8217;t play any other companion before you reach site 3.<br>
<br>
Go one site by one site each turn, unless you&#8217;re sure opponent may not slain your hobbits. By turn 2 or 3 you should have Boromir, Aragorn or Legolas in hand. They&#8217;ll reinforce your hobbits. You&#8217;ll have some archery to get rid of weak minions and combined with ARV, it helps a lot.<br>
<br>
Bilbo Baggins get you some Hobbit Stealth, Intuition and PATHS back each turn.<br>
<br>
Some card choices :<br>
Athelas : Anti Blade Tip and Black Breath, or may heal.<br>
Hobbit Intuition : i play 3 (instead of 2 Hobbit Stealth) because of the +3 Strength bonus allowing Merry to win many skirmishes with a strength of 10.<br>
Thror&#8217;s map : may replace sites. It&#8217;s especially nice if you are at site 8 and place your site 9 into play instead of opponent&#8217;s site 9 (if he&#8217;s not playing Sauron, of course).<br>
<br>
The shadow part&#8217;s goal is to slow opponent and hopefully kill him with exertion and archery combined.<br>
You also have many corruption cards to make sure your Enduring Evil are effective. (I put Aragorn strength &#8211;8 during a game). I only have 2 Hates, but it may be sufficient if you play them well.<br>
<br>
Some card choices :<br>
Enheartened Foe : As i only have one Morgul Hunter and BOTE, it may help if those minions become fierce. It may also help if you win a skirmish with any minion.<br>
Orc Inquisitor : low cost and annoying game text for opponent. Good Strength and vitality.<br>
<br>
Enjoy,<br>
<br>
Witch-King.<br>
